    "updated_at": "2016-04-19T15:48:36Z",
    "body": "Reading through the through https://github.com/brave/browser-laptop/issues/840, it seems that Brave is looking to track Chromium releases \"within a day or two\". I think Electron has been doing a great job of tracking Chromium releases, given the amount of work involved in updating and testing everything as underlying APIs change, but many Electron apps don't display external web content so the stated \"day or two\" turnaround time may not be as important for the broader Electron community. I imagine this lag time will be a recurring issue, and it may be worth looking for a broader solution for Brave than just rushing the Chromum 50 update.\n"
  },
