    "body": "@jsnar According to chromiums vulnerability disclosure policy.\n\nhttps://www.chromium.org/Home/chromium-security\n\nThey will automatically release vulnerabilities publicly 14 weeks after they are fixed.  Bearing in mind chrome has a 1-2 week release cycle and electron catches up in 1-2 weeks there is still a large buffer of time where the vulnerabilities are not public.\n\nAlso as @bengotow points out.  Most electron applications are not displaying web based content.\n"
