    "created_at": "2016-04-20T05:00:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-20T05:00:02Z",
    "body": "Frankly speaking, I don't think Electron team cares about security fixes: even staying at Chrome 49 it's still based on an old version 49.0.2623.75 instead of latest 49.0.2623.112. See how many security fixes with **high** importance in the later 49 versions here: http://googlechromereleases.blogspot.com/search/label/Stable%20updates\n\nI don't think rebasing from 49.0.2623.75 to 49.0.2623.112 takes much efforts as updating to 50. It's the matter of priority of dealing with security updates. And that should be fixed.\n"
  },
