    "created_at": "2016-04-20T21:27:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-20T21:31:46Z",
    "body": "> They will automatically release vulnerabilities publicly 14 weeks after they are fixed. Bearing in mind chrome has a 1-2 week release cycle and electron catches up in 1-2 weeks there is still a large buffer of time where the vulnerabilities are not public.\n\nIn reality this buffer is not dependable. Bug details can leak out in all sorts of ways before the report is public. The CVE details themselves may provide enough info for a smart attacker to exploit the vuln (ex: https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2016-1653 is out already). The best we can do is track Chromium updates closely.\n"
  },
