    "created_at": "2016-04-20T22:03:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-20T22:03:56Z",
    "body": "> Frankly speaking, I don't think Electron team cares about security fixes: even staying at Chrome 49 it's still based on an old version 49.0.2623.75 instead of latest 49.0.2623.112.\n\nTo be honest, we _don't_ care about security fixes, in the same way that Brave _has_ to care about security fixes. Most Electron apps either run local content, or run remote content but in a very specific way (i.e. Slack, which executes code from exactly _one_ site).\n\nIf Brave needs to have Chrome 50 literally the day it drops, they're going to have to do that engineering work - we'll certainly do our very best to accommodate that and get builds out the door quickly, but at the end of the day, Brave's on the hook for Brave's security model / risk, not the maintainers of Electron \n"
  },
