      "site_admin": false
    },
    "created_at": "2016-04-20T22:04:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-20T22:09:22Z",
    "body": "> This is very important for Brave project.\n\nI was always under the impression Brave forked Electron and used their own builds. I never built Electron myself but if this is the case they should be able to produce their own Chromium 50 build. \n\nPersonally, I always considered running third party content in Electron to be potentially dangerous. I think if anyone wants to run third party content, be a browser, etc they should fork Chromium and build off that. Not fork a fork of Chromium that is purposely designed to break sandbox restrictions.\n"
  },
