    "created_at": "2016-04-20T23:42:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-20T23:42:31Z",
    "body": "Don't get me wrong in general - supporting new versions of Chrome as soon as possible is absolutely part of our goals, but I want to dispel a notion right now that it's simply \"a rebase\", or just bumping a version, because that's far from accurate.\n\nIt is usually a **significant** amount of work to move to a new Chromium major version, involving hand-editing dozens or even hundreds of files. It is absolutely not free, and while contributors try to do their best to pitch in on this effort, at the end of the day it's still a significant effort.\n"
  },
