    "created_at": "2016-04-21T03:59:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-21T04:22:52Z",
    "body": "@diracdeltas This is why I want to stress the importance of my last sentence you left out of my quote. You are correct this is a big issue for programs like Slack or others that use third party content as \"trusted\". If Electron allows them to execute scripts in the node context it is game over. They have file system access and more. If nodeIntegration is disabled I still have concerns since Electron's security goals are not that of Chrome in order to make Electron work as intended. If the I's are not dotted and the T's are no crossed it could potentially be a very bad thing. This is why I think browsers built with Electron are a really bad idea and should be built off Chromium instead.\n\nElectron serves a very useful purpose. But if developers continue to misunderstand or misuse it they might as well straight up accept remote eval calls.\n"
  },
