    "created_at": "2016-04-21T04:41:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-21T04:44:04Z",
    "body": "> It's fine if you are not able to deliver a big secure chunk of code due to limited resources, but at least developers and end users should be warned if they are at risk.\n\nYou do understand Electron's goal isn't to protect users but to modify protections/sandboxing to allow web apps to interface in a more \"native\" way with Node.js right? There isn't much more warning needed than understanding your app is going to be in a browser with a Node.js context.\n\n@bbondy @jsnar I am not trying to come off as troll. But I feel like I am on crazy pills trying to stress using a project meant to break sandboxing/security to perform it's job is likely not a good platform where sandboxing/security should be considered priority.\n"
  },
