    "updated_at": "2016-04-21T04:55:15Z",
    "body": "@baconface it's not about sandboxing. Let me put it a simple way: imagine you develop a chat software, where users can post pictures in the channel, but the picture handling library you used have a bug dealing with the incoming picture data. It leads to buffer overflow and probably remote code execution. Would you ask the library developer to fix it?\n"
